      • logLevel

        public byte logLevel()
        Returns the log level used with this error. This is the log level value returned by the router. Since the number of log levels that the router uses is larger than the levels log4j API supports, some values are mapped to others. The effective log level can be retrieved by using effectiveLogLevel().
        Returns:
        The log level used with this error.
        See Also:
        XAResponseCodes

      • effectiveLogLevel

        public int effectiveLogLevel()
        Returns the effective log level used with this error. This value can be different than the log level indicated by the router since the router uses more log levels than the LOG4J API has. This method will return a value supported by the LOG4J API.
        Returns:
        The effective log level used with this error.
        See Also:
        XAResponseCodes
